SYNOPSIS
========
   float floor(floatÂ arg)

DESCRIPTION
===========
Round the <arg>ument downwards the nearest whole number, returning that value.
If the <arg>ument value is an integer, the result will be that value,
converted to float.

EXAMPLES floor(4.5)  - returns  4.0 floor(-4.5) - returns -5.0 floor(5)    -
returns  5.0

Introduced in LDMud 3.2.7. LDMud 3.2.9 added integers as argument values.

   See Also:
      abs(E), ceil(E)
